adminStakeEthForStEth(uint256).details: Used to earn yield on excess ETH held by the game.      SECURITY: Cannot stake ETH reserved for player claims (claimablePool).

adminSwapEthForStEth(address,uint256).details: Used to rebalance when stETH yield should be converted to ETH.      Admin must send exact ETH amount equal to stETH received.      SECURITY: Value-neutral swap, ContractAddresses.ADMIN cannot extract funds.

params.amount: ETH amount to swap (must match msg.value).

advanceGame(uint32).details: Anyone can call, but standard flows require an ETH mint today.      This is the primary driver of game progression - called repeatedly      to move through states and process batched operations.      FLOW OVERVIEW:      1. Check liveness guards (2.5yr deploy timeout, 365-day inactivity)      2. Apply daily gate (must have minted today unless cap != 0)      3. Process dormant cleanup if in setup state      4. Gate on RNG readiness (request new VRF if needed)      5. Process map mint batches      6. Run bond maintenance if pending      7. Execute state-specific logic (setup/purchase/degenerus)      8. Credit caller with BURNIE reward (if cap == 0)      SECURITY:      - Liveness guards prevent abandoned game lockup      - Daily gate prevents non-participants from advancing      - RNG gating ensures fairness (no manipulation during VRF window)      - Batched processing prevents DoS from large queues

params.cap: Gas budget override for batched operations.            0 = standard flow with BURNIE reward.            >0 = emergency unstuck mode (no BURNIE reward).

bondAvailable().details: Returns 0 if bondGameOver (funds drained to ContractAddresses.BONDS contract).

bondCreditToClaimable(address,uint256).details: Access: ContractAddresses.BONDS only. Moves funds from bondPool to claimablePool.      INVARIANT: bondPool >= amount (underflow reverts in Solidity 0.8+).

bondCreditToClaimableBatch(address[],uin.details: Access: ContractAddresses.BONDS only. Gas-optimized for multiple credits.      Aggregates total before single bondPool deduction.

bondDeposit(bool).details: Access: ContractAddresses.BONDS only.      If trackPool=true, adds to bondPool (tracked liability).      If trackPool=false, ETH falls through as yield (yieldPool treats excess as available).

params.trackPool: If true, credit to the tracked bondPool; if false, leave untracked as yield.

bondSpendToMaps(address,uint256,uint32).details: Access: ContractAddresses.BONDS only. Queues map mints for later processing.      Funds flow: bondPool  nextPrizePool (for jackpot distribution).

params.quantity: The number of maps to queue.

burnTokens(uint256[]).details: Access: any player during State 3 (DEGENERUS) when RNG is not locked.      For each token burned:      1. Extract 4 traits from token ID (deterministic hash)      2. Add ticket to each trait's burn pool for this level      3. Decrement trait remaining counts      4. Check for extermination (trait count hits threshold)      5. Track daily burn counts for jackpot calculations      6. Award bonus BURNIE for matching colors / carrying prev trait      BONUSES:       +4.9x BURNIE if all 4 traits share the same color category       +0.4x BURNIE if token has previous exterminated trait (or inverse on L90)       2x ticket count on L%10=2 (double count step)      EXTERMINATION:       Normally triggered when trait count = 0       On L%10=7, triggered when trait count = 1 (early end)       First token to trigger wins; remaining tokens skip

params.tokenIds: Array of token IDs to burn (1-75 tokens).

claimWinnings().details: Aggregates all winnings: affiliates, ContractAddresses.JACKPOTS, ContractAddresses.BONDS, endgame payouts.      Uses pull pattern for security (CEI: check balance, update state, then transfer).      GAS OPTIMIZATION: Leaves 1 wei sentinel so subsequent credits remain      non-zero  cheaper SSTORE (coldwarm vs coldzerowarm).      SECURITY: Reverts if balance  1 wei (nothing to claim).

constructor.details: All addresses are compile-time constants from ContractAddresses for gas optimization.      Infinite stETH approval to ContractAddresses.BONDS is safe as ContractAddresses.BONDS is a trusted contract.

creditDecJackpotClaim(address,uint256).details: Access: ContractAddresses.JACKPOTS contract only.      Silently returns if amount=0 or account=address(0).

params.amount: Wei amount associated with the claim.

creditDecJackpotClaimBatch(address[],uin.details: Access: ContractAddresses.JACKPOTS contract only.      Gas-optimized for multiple credits in single transaction.

params.accounts: Array of player addresses to credit.

decWindow().details: Window is only "on" if flag is set AND RNG is not locked.

returns.on: True if decimator entries are currently allowed.

returns.open: True if decimator window flag is set.

enqueueMap(address,uint32).details: Access: nft contract only.      Maps are processed in batches during advanceGame to prevent DoS.      If player already has maps owed, they're not re-added to pendingMapMints array.

params.quantity: Number of map entries to queue (1+).

returns._0: The level number (0 if never minted).
Number of distinct levels with ETH mints.

ethMintStats(address).details: Batches multiple stats into single call for gas efficiency.

returns._0: Number of consecutive levels with ETH mints.

returns.count: Number of tickets found in this page.

getTraitRemainingQuad(uint8[4]).details: Batched for gas efficiency when checking token traits.

returns.remaining: Array of remaining counts for each trait.

getWinnings().details: Returns 0 if balance is only the 1 wei sentinel.

returns._0: True if random word is available for use.

lastRngWord().details: Uses dailyIdx to locate the last completed day.

returns._0: The address that triggered extermination (address(0) if timeout or not reached).

mintPrice().details: Price varies by level cycle: 0.05/0.05/0.1/0.15/0.25 ETH.

nextPrizePoolView().details: Mint fees flow into nextPrizePool until target is met.

playerBonusMultiplier(address).details: 10000 bps = 1.0x multiplier. Max theoretical ~225% (22500 bps).      Components are additive and uncapped in aggregate.

params.player: The player address to calculate for.

prizePoolTargetView().details: Target is reset at level % 100 == 0 based on reward pool size.

purchaseInfo().details: Bundles level, state, flags, and price into single call.      NOTE: lvl is incremented in state 3 to show "next level" being played.

returns.gameState_: Current game state (0-3, 86 for game over).
returns.lastPurchaseDay_: True if prize pool target is met.
returns.lvl: Current level (or next level if in degenerus state).
returns.rngLocked_: True if VRF request is pending.

rawFulfillRandomWords(uint256,uint256[]).details: Access: VRF coordinator only.      Applies any queued nudges before storing the word.      SECURITY: Validates requestId and coordinator address.

recordCoinflipDeposit(uint256).details: Access: coin contract only.      Coinflip activity on last purchase day affects jackpot calculations.

params.amount: The wei amount deposited to coinflip.

recordMint(address,uint24,uint256,uint32.details: Access: nft contract only.      Payment modes:      - DirectEth: msg.value must exactly equal costWei      - Claimable: deduct from claimableWinnings (msg.value must be 0)      - Combined: ETH first, then claimable for remainder      SECURITY: Validates exact payment amounts to prevent over/underpayment.      Prize contribution flows to nextPrizePool for jackpot distribution.

params.costWei: Total cost in wei for this mint.
params.lvl: The level at which mint is occurring.
params.player: The player address to record mint for.

returns.coinReward: BURNIE reward credited for this mint.
returns.newClaimableBalance: Player's claimable balance after deduction (0 if DirectEth).

reverseFlip().details: Cost scales +50% per queued nudge and resets after fulfillment.      Only available while RNG is unlocked (before VRF request is in-flight).      MECHANISM: Adds 1 to the VRF word for each nudge, changing outcomes.      SECURITY: Players cannot predict the base word, only influence it.

rngLocked().details: When locked, burns and certain operations are blocked.

returns._0: True if RNG lock is active.

rngStalledForThreeDays().details: Enables emergency VRF coordinator rotation via updateVrfCoordinatorAndSub().

returns._0: True if no VRF word has been recorded for the last 3 day slots.

rngWordForDay(uint48).details: Days are indexed from JACKPOT_RESET_TIME offset.

returns._0: The random word (0 if no word recorded for that day).

sampleTraitTickets(uint256).details: Samples from last 20 levels. Uses entropy to select level, trait, and offset.      Returns empty array if no tickets exist for selected level/trait.

params.entropy: Random seed (typically VRF word) for selection.

returns.tickets: Array of up to 4 ticket holder addresses.

updateVrfCoordinatorAndSub(address,uint2.details: Access: ContractAddresses.ADMIN only. Only available when VRF has stalled for 3+ days.      This is a recovery mechanism for Chainlink outages.      SECURITY: Requires 3-day gap to prevent abuse.

params.newKeyHash: New key hash for the gas lane.

wireVrf(address,uint256,bytes32).details: Access: ContractAddresses.ADMIN only. Idempotent after first wire (repeats must match).      SECURITY: Once wired, config cannot be changed except via emergency rotation.

params.keyHash_: VRF key hash identifying the oracle and gas lane.
params.subId: VRF subscription ID for LINK billing.
